ly participate in all aspects of the rigorous VMI academic and physical program  After reviewing the initial medical packet  the Post Physician may request further records or a direct conversation with the applicant s physician and the applicant  If  after fully reviewing all the medical records along with information from the applicant  the student is determined to have a condition that may prevent full and safe participation in all aspects of VMI s program  the medical packet is reviewed by a Fitness Review Panel and forwarded to the Superintendent who makes the final decision  Program Requirements Physical Conditioning Standards at VMI  Required Immunizations Forms Please contact kingerylc vmi edu if you have further questions related to VMI medical requirements  Questions regarding commissioning should be directed to the specific ROTC branch of interest  VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu 